---
description: Global repo rules for all code generation
alwaysApply: true
---

You are working in a production-oriented Next.js + TypeScript + Vercel + Supabase + shadcn/ui codebase.

Follow these rules on every task:

- Prefer the smallest correct diff.
- Do not rewrite unrelated files.
- Keep code boring, readable, and maintainable.
- Default to App Router patterns.
- Default to Server Components. Add `"use client"` only when required.
- Keep strong TypeScript types. Avoid `any`.
- Prefer named exports for utilities. Use default exports only where framework conventions expect them.
- Preserve accessibility, keyboard navigation, and semantic HTML.
- Do not expose secrets, service role keys, or sensitive internals to the client.
- Do not fetch data in the browser if the same work can be done safely on the server.
- Reuse `@/lib/utils` helpers before adding new utility functions.
- When a change touches architecture, auth, env, or schema, mention tradeoffs and risks.
- If a rule cannot be followed, say exactly why.
